    <sec>
      <title>Application to the hb anterior activator</title>
      <p>The <italic>hb </italic>anterior activator (Figure <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F4">4a</xref>) responds to the Bcd gradient in the early <italic>D. melanogaster </italic>embryo [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B25">25</xref>]. It is thought to have been conserved since the divergence of <italic>D. melanogaster </italic>and <italic>D. virilis </italic>[<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B26">26</xref>] and contains well-defined binding sites for Bcd [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B27">27</xref>]. We therefore expect to see evidence of functional constraint on this regulatory region.</p>
